canonical:
  title: 再辭宜允
  author: 崔諴
  language: lzh
  text: 卿鈞軸重臣文章巨笔德望足以表儀百辟鑒識足以品藻群材甞倅掌於禮闈能見稱於物議首司厥任何有所難而再以抗章請其改命觀乎文義曲形推讓之誠強以賢勞恐非待遇之厚雖且從私便於今日必更授文柄於後年
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 再辭宜允
  author: 崔諴
  language: lzh
  text: 卿鈞軸重臣。文章巨笔。德望足以表儀百辟。鑒識足以品藻群材。甞倅掌於禮闈。能見稱於物議。首司厥任。何有所難。而再以抗章。請其改命。觀乎文義。曲形推讓之誠。強以賢勞。恐非待遇之厚。雖且從私便於今日。必更授文柄於後年。
korean:
  title: 재사 의윤
  author: 최함
  language: kor
  text: 경은 정부를 맡은 중신(重臣)이요, 문장을 맡은 거필(巨筆)이다. 덕망은 모든 신하들의 의표가 될 만하고, 감식(鑑識)은 여러 인재를 품평할 만하다. 그러므로 일찍 과거를 관장하여서 능히 물의에 칭찬받았으니, 그 임무를 수석으로 맡는 것이 무슨 어려울 바가 있기에, 재차 소를 올려서 임명을 고치라고 청하는가. 글을 살피매 간곡하게 사양하는 성의를 나타냈으니, 억지로 직무에 종사하기를 강요함이 도리어 후하게 대우하는 것이 아닐 듯하다. 이에 비록 오늘날에 사사 형편을 따르기는 하지마는, 반드시 후년에는 문병(文柄)을 다시 맡길 것이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0320_020_0100&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Second Petition to Decline the Post of Ceremonial Director
  author: Choe Ham
  language: eng
  text: You are a pillar of the state, a minister of weight and substance. Your literary talent commands a master's brush, and your virtue and wisdom stand as exemplars to all the officials. Your discernment is keen enough to appraise the talents of many. Having once overseen the civil examination halls, you earned universal praise for your stewardship. How could there be any difficulty in taking the lead in such duties? Yet you submit your petition a second time, requesting that your appointment be changed. In examining your words, I see only sincere and humble reluctance—but to force one of your talents into service would hardly show proper regard for your worth. Though I yield to your personal circumstances for now, I promise you shall receive the authority of letters again in years to come.
  footnotes:
    - '文柄 (the authority of letters): A metaphorical reference to high administrative positions, particularly those involving cultural or literary governance.'
    - This is an official response to a court memorial, likely addressed to a high-ranking minister declining a promotion or position.
